&lt;p&gt;The proposed front bay window extension would result in unsympathetic and visually obtrusive addition as this type of feature is not
prevailing within the immediate area, subsequently failing to respect the architecture and detailing of the host
building and the wider Becontree Estate which is a non-designated heritage asset. The proposed development is contrary to:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Paragraphs 131, 135, and 209 of the National Planning Policy Framework; (December 2023)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Policies D4 and HC1 of the London Plan (March 2021); &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Policies CP2 and CP3 of the Core Strategy&amp;nbsp;(July 2010);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Policies BP2 and BP11 of the Borough Wide Development Policies DPD&amp;nbsp;(March 2011);&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Policies SP 2, DMD 1, DMD 4, and DMD 6 of the draft LBBD Local Plan (&lt;/span&gt;December 2021); and&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document&amp;nbsp; (February 2012)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
